main event: A bright, circular, silver-sphere-like object was spotted flying low and fast over a residential area in Chicago, Illinois on June 27, 1957.
interesting points: The object appeared to be an 'ali' (unidentified) flying thing.
The object flew very low and fast over the residential area.
The witness, who was contacted at a fix parish driving north on Miami and Ave, was described as being 'shiky' (likely meaning shaky or nervous).
The sighting was reported to the Director of Intelligence and a 'Uncle C/Judge'.
The report was received on June 27th and filed as 3733.
